news.title: Mumbai clocks ₹1,101 crore from property registrations in July 2025
news.para: Mumbai's property market shows strong buyer confidence. In July 2025, property registrations reached 12,366. This generated ₹1,101 crore in revenue for Maharashtra. High-value transactions drove a stamp duty collection increase. Western and Central Suburbs dominated sales. Compact homes remained popular. Experts anticipate continued market momentum due to rate cuts and buyer-friendly plans.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance's profit rises 27.66% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Aptus Value Housing Finance India witnessed a 27.66% surge in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹219.25 crore in Q1 FY26. Total income grew by 31.02% to ₹530.14 crore. The company's AUM increased by 24% to ₹11,267 crore, with disbursements rising 15% to ₹775 crore, driven by a growing customer base and digital adoption.

news.title: Ambuja Cements' net profit up 23.81% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Ambuja Cements experienced a robust Q1 FY26, with a 23.81% increase in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹969.66 crore. The company's total income grew by 20.56% to ₹10,545.16 crore, driven by a 20% rise in cement sales volume. Ambuja Cements anticipates continued positive growth in the cement sector, projecting a 7-8% demand increase for FY26.

news.title: About 20,000 houses on Chennai's outskirts to get piped cooking gas
news.para: Chennai residents will soon have more access to piped natural gas. THINK Gas plans to connect 20,000 homes in the next 18 months. The expansion focuses on Old Mahabalipuram Road, Grand Southern Trunk Road, and southern outskirts. While infrastructure is ready, demand is a hurdle. The company seeks government support for a level playing field with LPG.

news.title: MPIDC allots plots to 23 against land pooling for sector 7 in Pithampur, Indore
news.para: Madhya Pradesh Industrial Development Corporation (MPIDC) has allotted commercial and residential plots worth approximately Rs 49 crore to 23 landowners in Pithampur's upcoming Sector 7 industrial area. This allotment, part of a larger land pooling initiative for the 2,090-hectare industrial expansion, follows a compensation model where landowners receive a mix of cash and developed plots.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body to ask plot owners to hand over roads for development work
news.para: The Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation (BMC) is urging developers and property owners to hand over previously earmarked roads to the civic body to facilitate planned development and infrastructure projects. This decision addresses instances where roads weren't transferred during property registration, hindering new road and drain construction.

news.title: Mumbai: Chawl residents up in arms as BEST attempts to cut power, water
news.para: Residents of Haji Noorani Chawl in Mumbai are facing harassment from BEST officials who attempted to disconnect their electricity and water supply. The action, allegedly requested by MHADA, cites safety concerns due to the Elphinstone Bridge construction.

news.title: Brigade Hotel Ventures shares drop nearly 10% in market debut trade
news.para: Brigade Hotel Ventures Ltd shares debuted on the stock exchanges with a nearly 10% discount to the issue price of Rs 90. The IPO, which was subscribed 4.48 times, involved a fresh issue of shares worth Rs 759.6 crore. The company intends to use the proceeds to reduce debt, acquire land, and support strategic initiatives.

news.title: Noida authority set to frame new policy for construction workers
news.para: Noida Authority is formulating a policy mandating developers and contractors to establish hygienic labor camps with essential amenities before commencing construction. This initiative aims to improve living conditions for the growing construction workforce by ensuring access to clean water, sanitation, electricity, and waste management.

news.title: Soon, law to prevent homes from being built illegally: Goa CM
news.para: Chief Minister Pramod Sawant announced that Goa will introduce legislation to prevent further illegal house construction. The government plans to reopen the window for locals to legalize existing houses on their land.

news.title: Telangana housing board sells one acre land in KPHB for over ₹65 crore
news.para: The Telangana government garnered over Rs 65.3 crore through the e-auction of an acre of commercial land in Kukatpally, with the ICAI winning the bid. Additionally, the state earned Rs 26 crore by selling Rajiv Swagruha Corporation flats in Bandlaguda, allotting 131 flats to middle-class beneficiaries via lottery.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh HC declines stay on land allotment to TCS in Visakhapatnam
news.para: The Andhra Pradesh High Court has refused to halt the land allotment to Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) in Visakhapatnam, noting that states often offer incentives to attract investments. While the court acknowledged concerns about the nominal land price, it emphasized the potential benefits of TCS's investment and job creation.

news.title: SC dismisses Zostel's appeal against Oyo
news.para: A bench comprising Justice Sanjay Kumar and Justice Satish Chandra Sharma dismissed Zostel’s special leave petition against the High Court order. The dispute traces back to 2015, when Oyo considered acquiring Zostel’s business including Zo Rooms.

news.title: Gujarat government proposes merger of five towns into Ahmedabad civic body limits
news.para: Ahmedabad is poised for significant expansion as the state government considers merging five surrounding municipalities—Sanand, Mehemdabad, Bareja, Kalol, and Dahegam—into the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC). This strategic move aims to enhance coordinated urban development and improve infrastructure in rapidly growing areas before the 2026 municipal elections.

news.title: SC wants early high court hearing on Haryana’s S+4 policy
news.para: The Supreme Court addressed a petition challenging Haryana's stilt+4 construction policy, directing the Punjab and Haryana High Court to consider interim relief requests. The petition raises concerns about the policy's impact on Gurgaon's infrastructure. The petitioner seeks a stay on new approvals and an oversight committee, highlighting the urgency of addressing urban expansion issues.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: 1% stamp duty relief to women buyers on properties up to Rs 1 crore
news.para: In Uttar Pradesh, women buying properties up to Rs 1 crore now benefit from a 1% stamp duty waiver, effective July 29. This revision, increasing the previous limit from Rs 10 lakh, aims to encourage female property ownership and financial inclusion. While benefiting mid-segment buyers, some feel the cap should be higher, especially in Noida.

news.title: About 10-50% hike in collector rates on cards in Panchkula
news.para: Panchkula is considering a significant hike in collector rates. The proposed increase ranges from 10% to 50% for the fiscal year 2025-2026. Residential and industrial properties could see the biggest jump. Sectors 4, 5, 6 (MDC), and 6-11 may face a 50% rise. Public objections are welcome until July 31. Monica Gupta encourages residents to submit their concerns.

news.title: Prayagraj development body to hold lottery system for flat allotment on August 5
news.para: The Prayagraj Development Authority (PDA) will conduct a transparent lottery on August 5 at 11:30 am to allocate flats across 12 residential schemes. Online applications were accepted from June 25 to July 15, with 154 eligible applicants registered.
